                <note rend="inline" type="source">625.5131/97a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 14, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. We are informed that the Franco-Chilean commercial convention of January 16,
                    1936, has received legislative approval in France. Without disclosing your
                    interest to the Foreign Office, please ascertain discreetly the legislative
                    status of the convention in Chile.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
